## Limitations

The report is limited by the availability of sources and the potential bias in historical interpretations. Some sources may present a Eurocentric perspective, and the complexity of the Crusades means that not all causes and effects can be comprehensively covered in a brief report. Additionally, the dynamic nature of historical scholarship means that new interpretations and findings could emerge, altering the current understanding of the Crusades.